VERSION_TRACKING - ORIC-1 Emulator
=====================================

Current Version: 1.0.0-beta.2
Release Date: 2026-02-22
Status: Beta (Video Integrated, Debug Export Available)

Version History:
----------------
- 1.0.0-beta.2 (2026-02-22): Video Integration & Debug Export (Sprint 15)
  * Video system integrated into emulator main loop
  * Charset ROM connected to video renderer
  * PPM/BMP/ASCII framebuffer export module
  * CLI: --screenshot, --screenshot-at, --frame-dump, --frame-dump-interval
  * 11 new video tests (PPM/BMP/ASCII export, text/HIRES render, ROM boot)
  * Test suite expanded to 159 tests (100% pass)

- 1.0.0-beta (2026-02-22): Testing & Optimization (Sprint 14)
  * ROM compatibility validated with real ORIC-1 BASIC 1.0 ROM
  * Reset vector ($F42D), IRQ ($0228), NMI ($022B) verified
  * ROM boot sequence validated: VIA init, screen RAM, zero-page setup
  * Performance benchmark: ~90+ MHz equivalent (target <100ms/1M cycles met)
  * Static analysis run with strict warning flags
  * Fixed memory map comment in memory.h (VIA at $0300-$030F)
  * Fixed strncpy truncation warnings in hostfs.c
  * Makefile targets: test-rom, valgrind, static-analysis
  * Test suite expanded to 148 tests (100% pass)

- 1.0.0-alpha (2026-02-22): All core subsystems implemented
  * Complete MOS 6502 CPU (151 opcodes, 13 addressing modes)
  * Memory system with ROM/RAM banking and I/O routing
  * MOS 6522 VIA with timers and interrupts
  * Keyboard matrix (8x8), cassette interface
  * Video system (text 40x28 + HIRES 240x200)
  * AY-3-8910 PSG audio (3 channels + noise + envelopes)
  * TAP cassette format support
  * Sedoric disk filesystem + FDC WD1793
  * Host filesystem sharing (HostFS + VFS)
  * Conversion tools (bas2tap, bin2tap, tap2sedoric)
  * Configuration system (.ini parser)
  * 136 unit/integration tests (100% pass)
  * Full emulation loop with I/O wiring

- 0.1.0-alpha (2026-01-31): Project initialization
  * Repository structure created
  * Initial architecture defined
  * Agile project management setup

Semantic Versioning:
-------------------
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH-LABEL
- MAJOR: Incompatible API changes
- MINOR: New functionality (backward compatible)
- PATCH: Bug fixes (backward compatible)
- LABEL: alpha, beta, rc, stable

